Random splitting of each tissue into three subsets¶

P28724_no_event and P9900_no_event have too few spots to split

In [7]:
cell_metadata <- tumour@meta.data
cell_metadata$sample_id2<-NA
cell_metadata$sampleid2<-NA

samples=unique(cell_metadata$sample_id)
nrg=3
for(i in c(1:length(samples))){
set.seed(i)
wo<-which(cell_metadata$sample_id==samples[i])
cell_metadata[wo,'sample_id2']<-paste(samples[i],sample(c(1:3),length(wo)
                                                        ,replace=T,prob=rep(1/nrg,nrg)),sep='_')
}

Tumour DE analysis¶

In [23]:
batch='Acrossbatch'
c1='no'
c2='yes'
#DE 
        y <- DGEList(counts(summed), samples=colData(summed)$sampleid2, group = factor(colData(summed)$condition))
        y
        keep <- filterByExpr(y, group=colData(summed)$condition, min.count = 3, min.total.count = 10) 
        summary(keep) #summary(keep): FALSE =  3937
        y <- y[keep,]
        
        y <- calcNormFactors(y)
        y$samples
        
        par(mfrow=c(2,3))
        for (i in seq_len(ncol(y))) {
            plotMD(y, column=i)
        }
        
        design <- model.matrix(~y$samples$group)
        design
        
        y <- estimateDisp(y, design)
        summary(y$trended.dispersion)
        #seems like not well fitted yet 
        plotBCV(y)
        fit <- glmQLFit(y, design, robust=TRUE)
        summary(fit$var.prior)
        summary(fit$df.prior)
        res <- glmQLFTest(fit, coef=ncol(design))
        summary(decideTests(res))
        
        gene=rownames(decideTests(res))[decideTests(res)==1]
        dat1=cbind(genes=gene,state=rep('Up',length(gene)))
        
        gene=rownames(decideTests(res))[decideTests(res)==(-1)]
        dat2=cbind(genes=gene,state=rep('Down',length(gene)))
        
        datone=rbind(dat1,dat2)
        
        assign(paste(batch,c1,c2,'genes',sep='_'),
          datone)
        assign(paste(batch,c1,c2,'res',sep='_'),
          res)
